Sentencas: Sr(Ti1-xFex)O3-delta (STF) is an alternative to Ni-based cermet fuel electrodes for solid oxide electrochemical cells (SOCs) that can provide an improved tolerance to redox cycling, fuel impurities, and hydrocarbon fuels.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance Investigation of Sr(Ti1-xFex)O3-δ Fuel Electrodes with Different Fe Contents for Solid Oxide Electrochemical Cells

Sentencas: Sr(Ti0.3Fe0.7)O3-delta electrodes were recently found to exhibit an excellent performance, but lower Fe contents have not been studied.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance Investigation of Sr(Ti1-xFex)O3-δ Fuel Electrodes with Different Fe Contents for Solid Oxide Electrochemical Cells

Sentencas: In this work, the electrochemical performance of STF-based fuel electrodes with 0.4 <= x <= 0.7 are explored in both full cells and symmetric cells at different fuel conditions.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance Investigation of Sr(Ti1-xFex)O3-δ Fuel Electrodes with Different Fe Contents for Solid Oxide Electrochemical Cells

Sentencas: The electrode performance in the fuel cell mode (3% H2O humidified hydrogen) became slightly worse as x decreased from 0.7 to 0.5; however, it was much worse at x = 0.4.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance Investigation of Sr(Ti1-xFex)O3-δ Fuel Electrodes with Different Fe Contents for Solid Oxide Electrochemical Cells

Sentencas: In the steam electrolysis mode from 50% H2O to 50% H-2, the change in the electrode performance showed a similar trend, and a more significant degradation in the performance was found at x = 0.4.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance Investigation of Sr(Ti1-xFex)O3-δ Fuel Electrodes with Different Fe Contents for Solid Oxide Electrochemical Cells

Sentencas: The worse electrochemical performance in a high-steam-concentration atmosphere is due to the higher electrode polarization and increased ohmic resistance.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance Investigation of Sr(Ti1-xFex)O3-δ Fuel Electrodes with Different Fe Contents for Solid Oxide Electrochemical Cells

Sentencas: These results indicate that STF electrodes with x = 0.5 have a reasonable electrochemical performance for SOC applications.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance Investigation of Sr(Ti1-xFex)O3-δ Fuel Electrodes with Different Fe Contents for Solid Oxide Electrochemical Cells
